title: U.S. Prosecutors Indict Cybersecurity Insiders Accused of BlackCat Ransomware Attacks

content.raw: Federal prosecutors in the U.S. have accused a trio of allegedly hacking the networks of five U.S. companies with BlackCat (aka ALPHV) ransomware between May and November 2023 and extorting them.
